          <list id="6" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="B Bullets">The <text styleclass="VariableName">direction</text> of the <text styleclass="Element">spline</text> at a <text styleclass="Interface">Node</text> is normal to its <text styleclass="Interface">spline-handles</text></li>
            <li styleclass="B Bullets">The <text styleclass="VariableName">Radius-of Curvature</text> of the <text styleclass="Element">spline</text> at a <text styleclass="Interface">Node</text><text styleclass="Element">&#32;</text>is proportional to the length of its <text styleclass="Interface">spline-handle</text></li>
            <li styleclass="B Bullets">The <text styleclass="VariableName">Radius-of-Curvature</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> of the</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Element">spline</text> at a <text styleclass="Interface">Node</text> is symmetrical to the two sides of its <text styleclass="Interface">spline-handle</text>.</li>
            <li styleclass="Body Text">You can add <text styleclass="VariableName">Constraints</text> to <text styleclass="VariableName">Nodes</text>, but not the <text styleclass="Element">Spline&apos;s</text> curve.</li>
